snippet.textDisplay:
*TRANSCRIPT LADDIES*


Top o' the mornin!


I'm Irish, Irish the Hedgehog!


I was going to meet up with me old friends Tilly and Sonk when suddenly, I thought, "Y'know, I've got a mouth on me for some good ol' praties..."


And so then I went down towards Station Square and I bump into Big and it's just like, "How's the Big size a ye?" and he's all like, "Irish! How in the name of Tikal are ye?"


And I'm just all "Y'know a story horse, how's it going? How's yer gran?" and then he's like "Sonk was just here but that idiot was nattering about nothin!"


And so then I thought of me old fella, and suddenly Big says "Get outta that garden!" -- and then I thought he might've gone stone mad, and maybe he's just sick as a box of frogs -- but then I'm thinking 'Well, with Big he's a few short of a full shilling now,' do y'know what I mean? And quite frankly, his mouth is the size of an outlaid skip and some say he's the owner of the Giant's Causeway.


And so finally I meet up with Tilly and he's STRESSIN and he's all in 'n out like a fiddler's elbow. And now, Tilly's one of the lads, y'know? But the chipper's field is still so far away at this point and I still want me spuds, but Tilly's waying with the fairies, and at this point sure anyways "Sure that's your mountain there," as they say.


And the rest of the day to yourself!


Happy Saint Paddy's Day!
